        generated by incorporating fluorescent (or otherwise
        modified) nucleotides during <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">PCR</ENAMEX>. <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">LM-PCR</ENAMEX> has been used in
        several studies, including a systematic genome-wide
        location analysis of <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">yeast transcriptional activators</ENAMEX> [ <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">10</NUMEX>
        ] , and an unbiased search for <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">E2F</TIMEX> binding sites in a
        subset of human <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">promoters</ENAMEX> [ <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">11</TIMEX> ] . Studies employing the
        R-<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">PCR</ENAMEX> approach include genome-wide analyses of silencing
