        <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">perspective</ENAMEX> as biases should be less severe due to the
        <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">linear</ENAMEX> nature of the amplification [ <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">19</TIMEX> ] .
        To improve the accuracy of microarray-based genome
        mapping protocols, we have developed a linear amplification
        protocol for <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">genomic DNA</ENAMEX>. This protocol uses a terminal
        transferase tailing step and <NUMEX TYPE="ORDINAL">second</NUMEX> strand synthesis to
